            "headline": "Fiduciary Investment Advisor| Value Investor| Certified Financial Planner| Professor of Finance",
            "summary": "Christian is an investment manager and the founder of KAMSouth, an independent Private Wealth Management firm dedicated to helping clients plan for retirement while investing with the goal of minimizing risk. \n\nRetirees typically work with Christian because of his dedication to building trusted relationships and his conservative value investment philosophy. He believes it's a privilege to help people on their journey to achieve a Return on Life.  \n\nMy goal is to maximize wealth and ensure retirement readiness for individuals and families.  I guide clients through the critical decisions needed to ensure they reach their financial objectives.    \n\nHaving spent the last 25 plus years assessing and managing the challenges facing today's retirees, I provide expert guidance to individuals and families in making critical decisions to ensure retirement readiness, as well to teach those already out of the workforce how to get the best return on their savings. \n\nMy company, KAMSouth offers highly personalized active Fiduciary investment management and retirement financial planning. Our goal is to deliver institutional-level money management services and combine those with comprehensive retirement planning so clients can receive a greater advantage with their capital.\n\nPrior to founding KAM South, I served as a managing director of a family office. As part of my 25 years of active investment management experience, I have also worked as an equity research analyst for a large institutional money manager and for a bank trust department, and as a financial analyst for a mutual fund complex.\n\nAreas of Expertise: Financial Planning & Analysis, Portfolio Management, Investment/Retirement Planning, Equity Research, Teaching. \n\nHobbies and Interests: I love Atlanta Braves baseball and taking my kids to SunTrust park. I enjoy golfing and working on my golf game.",
